The paper proposes a novel recurrent neural network architecture designed to model systems characterized by multiple characteristic timescales in their dynamics. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper focuses on system identification and time series prediction tasks, which could also place it in sub-categories related to control systems and signal processing, such as cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
